Pricing - Then & Now

Original (Street) Price: When first released in 2000, the dedicated arcade cabinet retailed around $4,500–4,900, based on listings from restored cabinet resellers  ￼

VintageArcade.net lists Gauntlet Legends at $4,495 with a $200 upgrade option for Dark Legacy (totaling ~ $4,695), and some show ~$4,895 as well  ￼

Collector/Resale Prices Today:

Standard restored units typically sell between $4,000–5,500. For instance, Gameroom Goodies lists a fully refurbished Dark Legacy cabinet at $4,495￼.

Premium or rare cabinets, including original parts or pristine condition, may command upwards of $8,000–11,000. A non‑Arcade-specialist site listed one at ~$11,200 retail (discounted to $8,500), though this may be an outlier due to bundled services  ￼.

Private sales/auctions tend to land around $1,000–1,500 in local deals, especially when open to conversion boards or disclaimers on condition (). More rare finds have been reported around $4,500
